.TH "_allow_idle" 9 "_allow_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_allow_idle \- enable DPLL autoidle bits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _allow_idle
.BI "(struct clk_hw_omap *clk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clk" 12
struct clk * of the DPLL to operate on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Enable DPLL automatic idle control.  The DPLL will enter low-power
stop when its downstream clocks are gated.  No return value.
REVISIT: DPLL can optionally enter low-power bypass by writing 0x1
instead.  Add some mechanism to optionally enter this mode.
